benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/simplePlan - Add a simple plan entry in the current version of the catalog

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC07, @TC12, @TC13, @TC19, @TC20, @TC21, @TC23, @TC24 cover successful creation with valid data.
Invalid Payload: @TC04, @TC05, @TC09, @TC10, @TC11, @TC15, @TC18 cover invalid or malformed data and error handling.
Duplicate Submission: @TC06 covers conflict with existing planId.
Missing Required Headers: @TC03 covers missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header.
Extra Fields: @TC07 covers unsupported fields in the request.
Empty Request Body: @TC08 covers empty payload.
Unsupported HTTP Method: @TC14 covers method not allowed.
Large Payloads: @TC15 covers very large data.
Add when catalog is empty or partially populated: @TC19, @TC20.
gaps: Authorization: No explicit tests for missing or invalid authentication headers.
Rate Limiting: No tests for handling multiple rapid requests.
Caching Behavior: No tests for cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Server Errors: No scenarios simulating database failures or internal errors.
Edge Cases for maximum field lengths and special characters beyond basic boundary tests.
recommendations: Add tests for authorization failures (missing/invalid credentials).
Include rate limiting and throttling scenarios to verify system resilience under load.
Test caching headers and validation of cache-related behaviors.
Simulate server errors such as database or service failures to verify error handling.
Expand boundary tests for maximum field lengths and special characters to ensure robustness.
